stix:STIX_Header.stix:Title: AA20-303Av3 North Korean Cyber Actors Targeting Vaccine and Virology Organizations
stix:STIX_Header.stix:Description:
This joint cybersecurity advisory is the result of analytic efforts among the Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency (CISA), the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI), and the United Kingdom (UK) National Cyber Security Centre (NCSC). Working with U.S. Government (USG) partners, CISA, FBI, and NCSC have identified malicious cyber activity by actors linked to the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (DPRK) targeting a number of pharmaceutical, vaccine, and virology organizations affiliated with Operation Warp Speed (OWS). The USG refers to malicious cyber activity by the DPRK government as HIDDEN COBRA. For more information on HIDDEN COBRA activity, visit https://us-cert.cisa.gov/northkorea.
CISA, FBI, and NCSC strongly encourage organizations with unauthorized network access related to this advisory to contact CISA, your local FBI field office, or NCSC immediately.
This STIX file contains indicators of compromise associated with this activity and should only be disseminated to the following organizations:
(1) Companies that are critical to COVID-19 response and recovery, in Australia, Austria, Canada, France, Germany, Netherlands, New Zealand, South Korea, United Kingdom, and United States (including Operation Warp Speed entities).
(2) Government cybersecurity agencies in Australia, Austria, Canada, France, Germany, Netherlands, New Zealand, South Korea, United Kingdom, and United States and trusted private sector cybersecurity partners that those agencies deem critical to COVID-19 response and recovery.
For more information about this activity, to include detection and mitigation recommendations, please see AA20-303A North Korean Cyber Actors Targeting Vaccine and Virology Organizations.
